dcterms:creator: Alex Krizhevsky
Geoffrey Hinton
dcterms:description: CIFAR-10 is a dataset consisting of 60,000 32x32 color images in 10 different classes, with 6,000 images per class. It is commonly used for training machine learning models in image classification tasks.
dcterms:title: CIFAR-10

dcterms:creator: Alex Krizhevsky
Geoffrey Hinton
dcterms:description: CIFAR-100 is similar to CIFAR-10 but contains 100 classes with 600 images each. It is used for more fine-grained classification tasks.
dcterms:title: CIFAR-100

dcterms:creator: Ya Le
Xuan Yang
dcterms:description: Tiny-ImageNet is a smaller version of the ImageNet dataset, containing 200 classes with 500 training images and 50 validation images per class. It is used for visual recognition tasks.
dcterms:title: Tiny-ImageNet
